1
00:00:20,150 --> 00:00:21,240
The Mohnyin rebels are invading.

2
00:00:21,283 --> 00:00:24,640
Royal Uncle sent a messenger to Hongsawadi for aid,

3
00:00:24,757 --> 00:00:27,680
- The most suitable man for this task is…
- It is Mingyi Swa, my own son.

4
00:00:28,670 --> 00:00:32,320
- Yes, Your Highness.
- If Mingyi Swa rises to the rank of General, what then?

5
00:00:32,857 --> 00:00:35,840
He is sending his own son straight to his death.

6
00:00:35,857 --> 00:00:38,760
I humbly volunteer to join the campaign with Mingyi Swa.

7
00:00:45,757 --> 00:00:49,080
Prince Nares intervened and took the head with his twin swords.

8
00:00:49,163 --> 00:00:52,000
Would Prince Nares be willing to demonstrate those twin blades?

9
00:00:52,064 --> 00:00:53,720
A sight for us to behold?

10
00:00:55,097 --> 00:00:57,320
The twin sword style of Phra Maha Thera Khanchong.

11
00:00:57,437 --> 00:01:00,280
Never taught to anyone else. I never thought he’d teach it to you.

12
00:01:00,730 --> 00:01:03,520
these twin blades secured victory for Hongsawadi

13
00:01:03,737 --> 00:01:05,017
and saved my very life.

14
00:01:05,257 --> 00:01:07,360
Prince Nares has committed no wrong, Your Majesty.

15
00:01:07,710 --> 00:01:09,840
Learning the Mon style of swordsmanship is no crime.

16
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:13,760
But it becomes a crime if one uses it to betray his friends.

17
00:01:19,703 --> 00:01:21,000
I ask of you now,

18
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:24,680
to swear before the sacred relics,

19
00:01:25,303 --> 00:01:27,480
that you will be a loyal friend for all time.

20
00:01:28,050 --> 00:01:29,520
Do you dare to take this oath?

21
00:01:37,663 --> 00:01:38,920
Let us swear this oath together.

22
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:42,040
If you do not betray me,

23
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,520
I shall not betray you.

24
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:46,601
Do you agree?

25
00:01:58,480 --> 00:01:59,481
Yes.

26
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:17,400
- I swear
- I swear

27
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:20,040
- before the sacred Shwemawdaw Pagoda.
- before the sacred Shwemawdaw Pagoda.

28
00:02:20,830 --> 00:02:22,000
We, Mingyi Swa

29
00:02:22,257 --> 00:02:23,258
and I, Nares,

30
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,560
- shall be loyal friends,
- shall be loyal friends,

31
00:02:25,723 --> 00:02:27,443
- bound by true sincerity,
- bound by true sincerity,

32
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:29,400
- and never to betray one another.
- and never to betray one another.

33
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,520
- Should either break this oath
- Should either break this oath

34
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,840
- let him die this very day or the next,
- let him die this very day or the next,

35
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:36,123
- and let his soul burn in the depths of hell,
- and let his soul burn in the depths of hell,

36
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:38,450
- never to be reborn again.
- never to be reborn again.

37
00:02:49,770 --> 00:02:50,771
Checkmate.

38
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,320
Father is furious.

39
00:03:22,763 --> 00:03:24,280
Nares has likely escaped once again.

40
00:03:26,277 --> 00:03:28,510
That death-defying captive is truly formidable.

41
00:03:33,543 --> 00:03:35,400
If I can eliminate him,

42
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,601
Father would surely be pleased.

43
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:05,901
[The Residence of Princess Suphankalaya]

44
00:05:12,210 --> 00:05:13,211
What was your name again?

45
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:16,200
You've told me many times, yet I always seem to forget.

46
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:22,000
The child is nearly a year old, and yet you still cannot remember.

47
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:26,770
King Bayinnaung bestowed the name,

48
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:28,081
Phunchi.

49
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:33,200
But if it is too difficult, just call her

50
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,522
Min A Htwe.

51
00:05:36,686 --> 00:05:37,687
Min A Htwe.

52
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,760
Min A Htwe.

53
00:05:41,283 --> 00:05:42,840
Min A Htwe, my niece.

54
00:05:45,377 --> 00:05:46,600
Mother sent word to say

55
00:05:47,143 --> 00:05:48,244
she wishes to see her granddaughter's face.

56
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:57,560
We have been away from home for many years now.

57
00:05:59,563 --> 00:06:01,240
I do not know when we shall ever return.

58
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:03,600
Have you ever tried asking for permission?

59
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:09,680
I know my place well.

60
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:12,790
I am a hostage.

61
00:06:14,790 --> 00:06:17,440
To whom should I show my face and beg for mercy?

62
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,600
I will not return…

63
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:44,950
as a captive of Hongsawadi.

64
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:52,200
But I shall return to Ayutthaya

65
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:55,040
as a person of Ayutthaya.

66
00:06:56,820 --> 00:06:59,400
And I shall never set foot in Hongsawadi again.

67
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:09,760
One day, Sister.

68
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:11,721
One day.

69
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:33,601
Come down, brother.

70
00:07:53,450 --> 00:07:54,520
Brother.

71
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:57,760
Brother.

72
00:08:00,857 --> 00:08:03,520
Help! Help!

73
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:05,480
Brother!

74
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:07,440
Help me!

75
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:09,681
Help me!

76
00:08:10,657 --> 00:08:11,658
Brother!

77
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:17,160
Help me! Help me!

78
00:08:18,890 --> 00:08:20,161
Brother!

79
00:08:22,563 --> 00:08:25,600
Help! Can anyone hear me?

80
00:08:25,897 --> 00:08:27,240
Someone, help me!

81
00:08:28,143 --> 00:08:29,144
Help me!

82
00:08:32,637 --> 00:08:35,720
Help me, I beg of you! I don't know how to row!

83
00:08:36,303 --> 00:08:37,560
The boat is going to capsize!

84
00:08:39,297 --> 00:08:41,920
Mingyi Naung! sit down first!

85
00:08:42,363 --> 00:08:45,044
You will fall into the water. I will go find someone to help.

86
00:08:50,917 --> 00:08:51,918
Hey!

87
00:08:58,477 --> 00:08:59,528
Help! Help!

88
00:09:00,683 --> 00:09:02,480
- Help! Help!
- Mingyi Naung!

89
00:09:02,997 --> 00:09:04,120
Help! Help!

90
00:09:05,697 --> 00:09:06,698
Help.

91
00:09:13,897 --> 00:09:16,080
Mingyi Naung! Mingyi Naung!

92
00:09:16,897 --> 00:09:17,898
Mingyi Naung!

93
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,480
Mingyi Naung! Mingyi Naung!

94
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:23,761
Mingyi Naung! Mingyi Naung!

95
00:09:30,543 --> 00:09:31,544
Prince Nares.

96
00:10:47,874 --> 00:10:50,600
Dam, how are you?

97
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:54,281
Sister.

98
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:57,561
Be careful.

99
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:04,400
Who... who was it that pulled me out?

100
00:11:07,097 --> 00:11:08,401
Mingyi Swa.

101
00:11:14,130 --> 00:11:15,131
Good heavens!

102
00:11:15,770 --> 00:11:16,920
What has happened here?

103
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:19,040
Prince Naresuan fell into the palace moat.

104
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,362
As for how it happened, I am still not certain.

105
00:11:23,041 --> 00:11:24,482
Apply the medicine and watch over His Highness closely.

106
00:11:25,310 --> 00:11:26,880
Do not make a scene or tell anyone yet.

107
00:11:28,103 --> 00:11:30,560
Once Prince Nares has regained consciousness, send someone to fetch me.

108
00:11:31,117 --> 00:11:32,118
Yes, Your Highness.

109
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,720
I went into the water to save Mingyi Naung,

110
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:48,121
But he struck me with his oar.

111
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:51,080
It was intentional. He meant to kill me.

112
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:54,680
Dam, what are you going to do?

113
00:11:54,823 --> 00:11:55,824
I will have my revenge.

114
00:11:57,920 --> 00:11:58,921
You cannot.

115
00:12:00,883 --> 00:12:03,120
You say a ten-year-old boy plotted to kill you?

116
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:04,903
Who would believe such a tale?

117
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:06,400
A child could not think of this alone

118
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,441
it was the elders who commanded it!

119
00:12:07,511 --> 00:12:10,201
And who else could be the power behind him?

120
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:15,640
Is it not his own father, Crown Prince Jaisingh?

121
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:20,721
Khun Phra Nai.

122
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:23,680
Go and summon Prince Mingyi Swa at once.

123
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:26,120
I shall go and petition King Bayinnaung.

124
00:12:26,450 --> 00:12:28,040
I need the Prince to stand as my witness.

125
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,641
- Yes, Your Highness.
- Stop.

126
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,121
Dam.

127
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:36,642
Think on this well.

128
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:41,280
To kill within the palace grounds is a breach of the Palace Law.

129
00:12:42,543 --> 00:12:45,800
Will Mingyi Swa truly stand as a witness against his own father and brother?

130
00:12:46,003 --> 00:12:47,441
When the punishment is death?

131
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:50,161
Your Highness,

132
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,200
if this matter is not brought to judgment,

133
00:12:52,601 --> 00:12:56,320
they may be emboldened to strike again in the days to come.

134
00:12:56,950 --> 00:12:58,120
They will certainly strike again.

135
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:01,881
You must flee.

136
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:05,321
I am no coward.

137
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:07,240
Whoever strikes me, I strike back!

138
00:13:07,323 --> 00:13:09,560
- Why must I flee?
- Not as a coward flees,

139
00:13:12,297 --> 00:13:14,280
But as a man who is free.

140
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:19,560
You are like a thorn in the side of Jaisingh.

141
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:23,320
In this lifetime, the two of you can never coexist under the same sky.

142
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:26,040
Why, then, should you continue to endure this?

143
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:41,400
Let us go home.

144
00:13:44,257 --> 00:13:45,560
The time has come.

145
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:06,720
Your reward.

146
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:12,880
Thank you, Your Majesty.

147
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:17,760
King Bayinnaung once said to me,

148
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:21,240
I love to collect gold,

149
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:24,541
Because your name is Suphankalaya.

150
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,120
How utterly absurd.

151
00:14:32,443 --> 00:14:34,120
Get these things out of here.

152
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:37,200
Exchange them for weapons,

153
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:38,921
and transport them to Prince Nares.

154
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:43,760
[Kuy Village]

155
00:14:49,131 --> 00:14:52,240
The dawn is near. I must depart.

156
00:14:56,243 --> 00:14:57,840
Are you certain that you will not come with me?

157
00:15:00,330 --> 00:15:01,690
In but a few hours,

158
00:15:02,403 --> 00:15:04,297
Hongsawadi will know of your flight.

159
00:15:05,303 --> 00:15:07,560
They will surely send an army to hunt you down.

160
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:10,360
Battle will be inevitable.

161
00:15:12,897 --> 00:15:14,040
I am but a woman,

162
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,241
and I have a nursing babe.

163
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:19,520
If I go with you, I will only be a burden that holds you back.

164
00:15:21,389 --> 00:15:24,600
But if His Majesty is enraged by my flight, he will surely punish you in my stead.

165
00:15:28,670 --> 00:15:30,000
Do not worry for me.

166
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:33,040
I can survive this.

167
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:39,121
Go now, and go safely.

168
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:43,240
Prostrate yourself before our parents in my stead.

169
00:15:56,503 --> 00:15:58,200
They are coming, Your Highness.

170
00:16:20,023 --> 00:16:22,520
All the people of Ayutthaya who were taken captive then…

171
00:16:23,430 --> 00:16:25,480
Every one of them shall follow me home.

172
00:16:37,110 --> 00:16:38,200
My brothers and sisters,

173
00:16:45,920 --> 00:16:47,720
we march from Hongsawadi this day,

174
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:49,480
never to return.

175
00:16:51,770 --> 00:16:53,560
The path ahead is grueling

176
00:16:54,160 --> 00:16:55,720
naught but steep canyons and jagged thorns.

177
00:16:56,423 --> 00:16:57,440
I ask only this

178
00:16:58,160 --> 00:17:00,000
that you stand as one.

179
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:03,040
United, the difficult shall become easy,

180
00:17:03,921 --> 00:17:05,880
and the heavy shall become light.

181
00:17:06,263 --> 00:17:07,640
Yes, Your Highness!

182
00:17:10,697 --> 00:17:12,080
Everyone, make ready.

183
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:15,560
As soon as it is light enough to see the lines on your palms,

184
00:17:16,840 --> 00:17:18,041
we move out.

185
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:20,481
Wait.

186
00:17:36,077 --> 00:17:38,640
Your Holiness has followed us all this way. What is your purpose?

187
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:40,600
I believe

188
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:43,401
there are Mon people here in Hongsawadi

189
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:46,280
who are deeply troubled.

190
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:48,680
They find no happiness in staying.

191
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:53,240
They are men of skill and knowledge.

192
00:17:54,677 --> 00:17:56,720
I wish to entrust them to your service, that they may follow you.

193
00:17:59,110 --> 00:18:00,920
And what of you, Your Holiness?

194
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:04,000
If your heart holds no loyalty to this place,

195
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:06,361
why linger here in Hongsawadi?

196
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:09,800
I still have matters to attend to.

197
00:18:12,103 --> 00:18:15,604
I bless you, that you may succeed in all your aims

198
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:18,240
and be kept safe from every harm.

199
00:18:21,270 --> 00:18:22,271
Amen.

200
00:18:40,363 --> 00:18:41,680
I’ve come to bid you two farewell.

201
00:18:58,040 --> 00:18:59,440
And Muang as well.

202
00:19:06,862 --> 00:19:07,863
Muy.

203
00:19:09,040 --> 00:19:10,641
I'm leaving Muang in your care.

204
00:19:12,717 --> 00:19:14,360
I can care for his body, but not his spirit.

205
00:19:15,023 --> 00:19:16,600
He is already heartsick,

206
00:19:17,224 --> 00:19:18,840
knowing you depart.

207
00:19:24,610 --> 00:19:26,500
Can he not go with you, Your Highness?

208
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,280
That cannot be.

209
00:19:29,361 --> 00:19:32,760
Muang is registered as a royal elephant now, no longer a wild one.

210
00:19:33,362 --> 00:19:36,720
If he follows Your Highness, those left behind will be held guilty.

211
00:19:37,363 --> 00:19:38,800
Our whole house would lose our heads.

212
00:19:42,677 --> 00:19:44,640
Then why stay here waiting for the blade?

213
00:19:46,230 --> 00:19:47,880
Move with Muang and follow me.

214
00:19:52,643 --> 00:19:54,157
Can we, Your Highness?

215
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:55,481
You can.

216
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:59,200
The land where I am going has plenty of elephants for you to tend.

217
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,000
Then let us go!

218
00:20:03,203 --> 00:20:05,640
Did you hear that, Muang? We’re going together!

219
00:20:13,390 --> 00:20:15,840
We won't be coming back to Hongsawadi this time.

220
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:18,480
That fifth-month liquor you buried,

221
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:20,720
dig it all up for me.

222
00:20:21,161 --> 00:20:22,960
And don't you dare hide a single drop.

223
00:20:24,280 --> 00:20:25,281
Yes, Your Highness!

224
00:20:43,770 --> 00:20:44,771
Sister.

225
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:48,000
I’ll be back for you soon.

226
00:21:24,020 --> 00:21:25,400
Take care of yourself.

227
00:21:36,930 --> 00:21:38,120
Go quickly.

228
00:22:09,563 --> 00:22:10,564
Go.

229
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:31,200
Has he herded every last soul from Ayutthaya away?

230
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:34,201
How dare him!

231
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:39,800
By doing this, Nares is committing blatant treason.

232
00:22:43,370 --> 00:22:45,880
What say you, Suphankalaya?

233
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:47,960
Your younger brother

234
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:51,640
leading people out of Hongsawadi like this. What is his aim?

235
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:55,321
I do not know what is in Prince Nares’s mind, my Lord.

236
00:22:56,803 --> 00:22:59,640
But I am certain

237
00:22:59,917 --> 00:23:03,440
he harbors no ill will toward you, nor toward Hongsawadi.

238
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:09,920
I know the reason why.

239
00:23:13,930 --> 00:23:16,931
Yesterday, an attempt was made on Prince Nares’s life.

240
00:23:18,670 --> 00:23:20,640
I believe that is why

241
00:23:20,717 --> 00:23:22,040
His Highness has fled, Your Majesty.

242
00:23:22,080 --> 00:23:23,081
Nonsense!

243
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:29,480
I crave your royal permission

244
00:23:29,577 --> 00:23:32,000
to raise an army and crush Nares’s rebellion.

245
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:34,486
I shall bring him back to face judgment,

246
00:23:34,537 --> 00:23:36,560
that he may serve as a warning to all who follow.

247
00:23:38,070 --> 00:23:40,440
By your grace, if that is the case,

248
00:23:41,071 --> 00:23:44,330
I beg leave to lead the army myself and bring Prince Nares back, Your Highness.

249
00:23:46,723 --> 00:23:47,724
This is a small matter.

250
00:23:49,017 --> 00:23:51,800
There is no need for the Crown Prince to lead an army for such a thing.

251
00:23:52,943 --> 00:23:56,720
Mingyi Swa, go after Nares and bring his people back.

252
00:23:57,440 --> 00:24:00,880
I shall not hold him at fault, but if he resists,

253
00:24:02,023 --> 00:24:03,400
I shall deem it treason,

254
00:24:04,723 --> 00:24:06,960
punishable by death.

255
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,920
As you command, Your Majesty.

256
00:24:49,090 --> 00:24:50,360
Do you remember me?

257
00:24:53,363 --> 00:24:54,600
You... elephant child.

258
00:24:58,557 --> 00:24:59,640
Prince Mingyi Swa.

259
00:25:01,240 --> 00:25:02,280
Go and tell Prince Nares.

260
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:05,160
I will be waiting by the great tree,

261
00:25:05,560 --> 00:25:06,840
near the stream over there.

262
00:25:09,543 --> 00:25:11,044
Tell him to come and negotiate,

263
00:25:12,203 --> 00:25:15,560
so that we need not trouble our men to slaughter each other for nothing.

264
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:55,121
Brother.

265
00:26:01,280 --> 00:26:02,281
Brother.

266
00:26:05,510 --> 00:26:06,800
I left in such haste.

267
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:09,480
I did not even have the chance to thank you for saving my life.

268
00:26:12,263 --> 00:26:13,264
Think nothing of it.

269
00:26:14,560 --> 00:26:18,000
You once saved me, too. Let us consider the debt settled.

270
00:26:23,150 --> 00:26:26,560
Have you truly come to capture me yourself?

271
00:26:30,390 --> 00:26:32,040
I wanted to hear it from your own lips.

272
00:26:33,320 --> 00:26:34,840
Why did you flee?

273
00:26:37,683 --> 00:26:39,524
I was lured into a trap by Mingyi Naung to be assassinated.

274
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:44,680
And I suspect the Crown Prince Jaisingh is the one pulling the strings behind it all.

275
00:26:50,990 --> 00:26:52,760
But you did not flee alone.

276
00:26:54,080 --> 00:26:57,280
You brought our people with you. To do so,

277
00:26:57,830 --> 00:27:00,400
- is nothing less than an act of rebellion against Hongsawadi.
- I only wanted to go home.

278
00:27:01,260 --> 00:27:02,640
I only wish to be in my own place.

279
00:27:03,440 --> 00:27:06,080
A place to sleep in peace, without the constant fear of death.

280
00:27:08,757 --> 00:27:10,640
If this is what you call rebellion,

281
00:27:13,363 --> 00:27:14,720
then a rebel I shall be.

282
00:27:16,677 --> 00:27:19,880
But the penalty for treason is death.

283
00:27:22,850 --> 00:27:24,440
If you want my life,

284
00:27:29,837 --> 00:27:30,960
then come and take it.

285
00:27:45,017 --> 00:27:47,077
Do you remember our word?

286
00:27:48,383 --> 00:27:49,800
If you stood by me,

287
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:52,480
I would stand by you.

288
00:27:54,330 --> 00:27:55,331
Now

289
00:27:57,377 --> 00:27:58,680
does that still hold true?

290
00:28:07,943 --> 00:28:11,160
I have come, and I cannot return empty-handed.

291
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:17,720
The Hongsawadi army will wait until tomorrow.

292
00:28:19,163 --> 00:28:21,520
At dawn, we will storm and destroy your camp.

293
00:28:24,750 --> 00:28:26,400
I will move my people tonight.

294
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:29,320
I'll leave some weapons and supplies behind.

295
00:28:31,030 --> 00:28:32,400
Take them back with you, as your prize.

296
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:36,561
Nares.

297
00:28:52,230 --> 00:28:53,760
May you be safe.

298
00:29:33,683 --> 00:29:37,560
Sent for them, yet you return alone. Why?

299
00:29:39,877 --> 00:29:42,920
Prince Nares abandoned camp and fled with his people overnight.

300
00:29:43,910 --> 00:29:45,320
I could not catch him, Your Majesty.

301
00:29:46,630 --> 00:29:49,550
Outpaced? Or did you let him go?

302
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:57,360
Scouts report Prince Nares heading east,

303
00:29:57,677 --> 00:29:59,500
likely for Phitsanulok.

304
00:30:00,770 --> 00:30:02,640
Since Mingyi Swa failed,

305
00:30:03,120 --> 00:30:06,840
I volunteer to lead the pursuit and bring him to justice myself.

306
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:10,360
It is well, Your Majesty.

307
00:30:11,883 --> 00:30:13,561
Once Prince Naresuan is brought back,

308
00:30:14,300 --> 00:30:15,840
the truth of his flight

309
00:30:16,623 --> 00:30:18,120
shall be revealed.

310
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:28,160
Grandfather shall judge for yourself

311
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:32,040
if an attempt was made on Prince Nares’s life within the palace walls,

312
00:30:34,080 --> 00:30:35,320
what should the penalty be?

313
00:30:36,510 --> 00:30:37,511
Who?

314
00:30:38,943 --> 00:30:40,520
Who dared to attempt Nares's life?

315
00:30:41,470 --> 00:30:43,520
From whom did you hear such lies?

316
00:30:49,071 --> 00:30:50,072
Prince Nares.

317
00:30:58,080 --> 00:30:59,800
I saw it with my own eyes.

318
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:04,401
Mingyi Naung struck Prince Nares unconscious

319
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:06,360
and left him to drown.

320
00:31:10,121 --> 00:31:11,674
Had I not saved him,

321
00:31:12,520 --> 00:31:14,321
he would be dead.

322
00:31:18,697 --> 00:31:19,720
How dare you!

323
00:31:21,040 --> 00:31:22,880
To kill within the palace walls,

324
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:27,120
has the law lost all meaning?

325
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:30,881
Jaisingh.

326
00:31:32,303 --> 00:31:34,520
Is this how you raise your son?

327
00:31:39,103 --> 00:31:42,600
To eliminate an enemy,

328
00:31:42,704 --> 00:31:43,877
I will do whatever it takes.

329
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:49,040
After those words,

330
00:31:52,470 --> 00:31:56,040
if I were Naresuan, why would I ever return?

331
00:32:03,250 --> 00:32:05,320
I beg your royal pardon.

332
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:06,881
What is it?

333
00:32:06,950 --> 00:32:09,800
King Maha Thammaracha has arrived.

334
00:32:10,160 --> 00:32:13,661
He requests an audience.

335
00:32:13,700 --> 00:32:14,701
To discuss an urgent state matter, Your Majesty.

336
00:32:32,830 --> 00:32:34,577
The Junior Queen sent word that

337
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:37,440
Prince Nares fled after an attempt on his life.

338
00:32:38,463 --> 00:32:40,760
In my distress, I have come at once.

339
00:32:42,550 --> 00:32:43,920
It is nothing.

340
00:32:45,637 --> 00:32:47,840
The children simply do not get along.

341
00:32:48,537 --> 00:32:52,077
My grandson was out of line, provoked Naresuan until he was injured.

342
00:32:53,037 --> 00:32:55,338
It was merely a childish spat.

343
00:32:57,383 --> 00:32:59,320
If he is capable of this at ten,

344
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:04,400
Nares will surely not survive adulthood.

345
00:33:05,843 --> 00:33:08,600
As a father, I cannot help but fear for him.

346
00:33:14,523 --> 00:33:16,400
If Your Majesty possesses any mercy,

347
00:33:17,050 --> 00:33:19,150
I beg your permission

348
00:33:20,330 --> 00:33:23,120
to let Nares return to Phitsanulok.

349
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:26,800
There, he can focus on his loyalty to you,

350
00:33:27,480 --> 00:33:29,840
without further cause for resentment or strife.

351
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:48,001
[Chan Royal Palace, Phitsanulok]

352
00:33:50,570 --> 00:33:54,000
In the auspicious year 933,

353
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:55,600
the Year of the Goat,

354
00:33:56,203 --> 00:33:58,600
By Royal Command,

355
00:33:58,960 --> 00:34:03,250
Somdet Phra Chao Sanphet Wongkura Suriyodom,

356
00:34:03,730 --> 00:34:07,160
Borom Maha Thammarachathirat Rames,

357
00:34:07,617 --> 00:34:10,640
Pawaret Dhammikarat Dechochai,

358
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:13,880
Phrommathep Adithep Narubodintra,

359
00:34:14,403 --> 00:34:18,840
Phuminthara Thep Sommutirat Borommapophit,

360
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:23,623
appoints Prince Narayana

361
00:34:23,943 --> 00:34:27,080
to ascend the throne and rule the City of Phitsanulok.

362
00:34:28,530 --> 00:34:30,240
Long Live the King!

363
00:36:49,370 --> 00:36:52,280
My thanks to you, Phet and Sri, for helping me train the troops.

364
00:36:55,160 --> 00:36:56,161
[Phra Ratchamanu]

365
00:36:56,261 --> 00:36:57,262
[Phet]

366
00:36:58,600 --> 00:37:00,280
It is we who must thank Your Highness,

367
00:37:00,623 --> 00:37:02,280
for never forgetting old friends like us.

368
00:37:02,300 --> 00:37:03,301
[Phra Sri Thamorat]

369
00:37:03,335 --> 00:37:04,336
[Sri]

370
00:37:04,340 --> 00:37:06,520
How could I ever forget? When we were children,

371
00:37:06,917 --> 00:37:08,320
we used to chase chickens together.

372
00:37:12,120 --> 00:37:14,880
As children, we chased chickens. But now?

373
00:37:15,103 --> 00:37:16,897
Now, we're climbing, diving, and wallowing in mud.

374
00:37:17,150 --> 00:37:20,160
Are you training soldiers or bandits, Your Highness?

375
00:37:25,523 --> 00:37:26,524
Our numbers are few.

376
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:30,560
If the Hongsawadi army marches on us, how could we ever withstand them?

377
00:37:31,190 --> 00:37:33,800
It is by these bandit tactics alone that we will survive.

378
00:37:36,063 --> 00:37:37,920
Will Hongsawadi truly march against us, Your Highness?

379
00:37:45,017 --> 00:37:46,720
If I play the part of a good child,

380
00:37:47,483 --> 00:37:50,440
A humble vassal who bows to their every whim,

381
00:37:51,343 --> 00:37:52,600
they would surely stay their hand.

382
00:38:02,070 --> 00:38:04,840
But as they say, I have never been a good child.

383
00:38:19,480 --> 00:38:21,040
Without me in Hongsawadi,

384
00:38:22,350 --> 00:38:25,600
Mingyi Swa will surely go back to being a good child himself.

385
00:39:39,623 --> 00:39:40,640
The music is so beautiful.

386
00:39:42,203 --> 00:39:44,680
Why have you stopped?

387
00:39:48,960 --> 00:39:52,800
Mingyi Swa, why have you come empty-handed? Where is your lute?

388
00:39:53,880 --> 00:39:55,920
How are we to continue our duet if you've brought no music?

389
00:39:58,640 --> 00:40:00,040
Today, I am too weary to play.

390
00:40:02,437 --> 00:40:04,280
I would rather simply listen to my heart's content.

391
00:40:06,983 --> 00:40:09,240
For who knows how long it will be

392
00:40:11,317 --> 00:40:12,400
before I hear your lute again.

393
00:40:28,970 --> 00:40:30,480
Where do you intend to go?

394
00:40:34,323 --> 00:40:37,080
King Setthathirath of Lan Xang has passed.

395
00:40:38,957 --> 00:40:42,280
Phraya Saen Surintha Luechai, the Grand Minister, has seized the throne.

396
00:40:43,480 --> 00:40:45,480
Furthermore, the Crown Prince of Lan Xang

397
00:40:45,817 --> 00:40:47,720
is still held hostage here in Hongsawadi.

398
00:40:48,760 --> 00:40:50,200
Grandfather deems this an injustice,

399
00:40:50,880 --> 00:40:52,840
so he will march his armies to reclaim the kingdom.

400
00:40:55,917 --> 00:40:57,120
Mingyi Swa.

401
00:40:58,800 --> 00:41:00,440
Do you intend to join the battle as well?

402
00:41:03,170 --> 00:41:04,771
Grandfather has issued a decree.

403
00:41:05,840 --> 00:41:07,400
My father is to stay and guard the city,

404
00:41:09,770 --> 00:41:12,160
while Minye Kyawswa and I are sent to fight in his stead.

405
00:41:21,370 --> 00:41:22,640
I have no love for war.

406
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:28,641
I loathe the thought of having to take the lives of others.

407
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:44,800
To be born a man is to be born with duty.

408
00:41:47,720 --> 00:41:49,600
We cannot simply follow the whims of our own hearts.

409
00:42:02,640 --> 00:42:03,641
In this one life I have,

410
00:42:06,177 --> 00:42:07,360
I ask for only one thing.

411
00:42:09,440 --> 00:42:11,240
That just once, I may follow my own heart.

412
00:42:27,470 --> 00:42:28,670
Mingyi Swa.

413
00:42:43,373 --> 00:42:44,880
This campaign against Lan Xang,

414
00:42:46,577 --> 00:42:48,160
it does have its advantages, I suppose.

415
00:42:51,040 --> 00:42:55,440
Grandfather orders Ayutthaya and Phitsanulok to join the war.

416
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:07,320
At last, I shall see Naresuan’s face once more.

417
00:43:15,083 --> 00:43:18,960
I led my men from Phitsanulok to Nong Bua,

418
00:43:19,810 --> 00:43:21,440
The gateway to Lan Xang,

419
00:43:21,763 --> 00:43:23,360
to await the forces from Ayutthaya.

420
00:43:28,280 --> 00:43:32,240
From there, we were to join King Bayinnong's great army.

421
00:43:34,217 --> 00:43:36,560
But fortune has turned against me.

422
00:44:06,343 --> 00:44:09,040
Sri! Phet! Look, a fire over there.

423
00:44:20,623 --> 00:44:22,043
This was once a village.

424
00:44:22,720 --> 00:44:23,800
Everything is burnt to the ground.

425
00:44:25,160 --> 00:44:26,161
Where have all the people gone?

426
00:44:28,050 --> 00:44:29,960
Help.

427
00:44:32,877 --> 00:44:33,878
Help.

428
00:44:36,070 --> 00:44:37,071
Go!

429
00:44:41,563 --> 00:44:42,564
Grandmother.

430
00:44:47,477 --> 00:44:48,478
Grandmother.

431
00:44:49,240 --> 00:44:50,241
What is the matter?

432
00:44:50,583 --> 00:44:53,800
The plague has struck. Everyone is dead.

433
00:44:54,120 --> 00:44:57,000
So they burned the village to the ground.

434
00:44:59,283 --> 00:45:00,800
Has the plague struck here, Grandmother?

435
00:45:03,357 --> 00:45:06,203
Grandmother! Grandmother!

436
00:45:07,003 --> 00:45:09,000
- Your Highness.
- What?

437
00:45:10,570 --> 00:45:11,571
Look.

438
00:45:42,237 --> 00:45:43,238
Your Higness.

439
00:45:43,290 --> 00:45:44,291
Move.

440
00:46:26,170 --> 00:46:28,720
Is there any improvement, Phra Ratchamanu?

441
00:46:31,483 --> 00:46:34,400
He is stricken with a high fever; his body is burning up.

442
00:46:34,857 --> 00:46:36,480
His condition has worsened, Your Majesty.

443
00:46:40,930 --> 00:46:42,720
Is it smallpox that has stricken Prince Nares?

444
00:46:43,040 --> 00:46:44,041
Yes, Your Highness.

445
00:46:45,063 --> 00:46:47,084
Smallpox has no cure.

446
00:46:47,640 --> 00:46:50,440
Worse still, anyone who draws near

447
00:46:50,750 --> 00:46:52,160
will surely catch it.

448
00:46:54,690 --> 00:46:56,800
It seems the entire camp is destined to perish together.

449
00:47:00,317 --> 00:47:01,440
Phra Sri Thamorat,

450
00:47:02,510 --> 00:47:04,760
Return to King Maha Thammaracha at once.

451
00:47:05,637 --> 00:47:07,600
Tell him we command his army to halt exactly where they are.

452
00:47:07,917 --> 00:47:09,880
He must not bring his forces to join us.

453
00:47:10,230 --> 00:47:11,360
By your command, Your Majesty.

454
00:47:12,160 --> 00:47:16,200
Use all your strength to care for Prince Nares.

455
00:47:17,170 --> 00:47:18,760
If you lack anything, let me know.

456
00:47:19,600 --> 00:47:21,001
I will provide whatever is needed.

457
00:47:22,930 --> 00:47:24,200
Your kindness is most gracious, Your Majesty.

458
00:47:45,937 --> 00:47:46,938
Bring me my horse.

459
00:47:50,650 --> 00:47:54,120
Are you going to see that captive, Brother?

460
00:47:58,650 --> 00:48:00,120
This does not concern you.

461
00:48:02,983 --> 00:48:03,984
Brother.

462
00:48:06,157 --> 00:48:07,920
If you venture outside the camp

463
00:48:08,640 --> 00:48:10,200
and bring back calamity,

464
00:48:10,370 --> 00:48:11,920
then it most certainly concerns me.

465
00:48:13,483 --> 00:48:14,484
Soldiers!

466
00:48:15,610 --> 00:48:17,760
If General Mingyi Swa goes out,

467
00:48:18,240 --> 00:48:19,920
he will bring the smallpox back with him.

468
00:48:20,920 --> 00:48:22,840
Under no circumstances must he be allowed to leave!

469
00:48:33,670 --> 00:48:34,671
You.

470
00:48:35,950 --> 00:48:37,320
Only one in a hundred

471
00:48:38,560 --> 00:48:41,880
survives the smallpox.

472
00:48:43,640 --> 00:48:45,280
Wait for the news, Brother.

473
00:48:45,760 --> 00:48:48,161
Then, you may perform the merit-making

474
00:48:48,790 --> 00:48:51,880
for your sworn brother later.

475
00:49:07,960 --> 00:49:09,560
My condition has taken a turn for the worse.

476
00:49:13,597 --> 00:49:16,400
My father has ordered the retreat

477
00:49:16,800 --> 00:49:18,520
to take me back to Phitsanulok.

478
00:50:10,550 --> 00:50:14,320
Everyone believes, without a doubt, that I am going to die.

479
00:50:23,997 --> 00:50:27,120
Song Kwae, a paradise between two rivers.

480
00:50:27,640 --> 00:50:28,920
It truly lives up to its name.

481
00:50:29,520 --> 00:50:32,960
Phitsanulok is my home. Hongsawadi is not.

482
00:50:34,160 --> 00:50:36,560
If I hope to see this kingdom live in peace and prosperity,

483
00:50:36,797 --> 00:50:38,920
then you cannot leave it in your father's hands.

484
00:50:40,950 --> 00:50:42,730
The Great Hongsawadi

485
00:50:43,320 --> 00:50:47,243
was built with every drop of my blood and every scar upon my body.

486
00:50:47,303 --> 00:50:50,240
You cannot give it to anyone else. I will not allow it!

487
00:50:51,990 --> 00:50:54,920
Whether Hongsawadi shall know peace,

488
00:50:55,800 --> 00:50:57,040
or be consumed by flames,

489
00:50:58,520 --> 00:50:59,800
that now rests entirely with you.
